{
  "name": "Heroic Leap",
  "type": "technique",
  "img": "icons/magic/control/debuff-energy-hold-levitate-yellow.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>Using a Melee Weapon or Unarmed Strike, you can spend <strong>1 AP</strong> and <strong>1 SP</strong> to perform an exceptional leap and assault a creature.</p><p>You gain up to your <strong>Speed </strong>in Spaces and increase your <strong>Jump Distance </strong>by 1 on the next Long or Vertical Jump you make.</p><p>You leap into the air and make an <strong>Attack Check </strong>against a target in range, and the target makes a <strong>Physical Save</strong>.</p><p><strong>Attack Hit: </strong>It takes your Weapons damage.</p><p><strong>Failure: </strong>The target falls <strong>Prone</strong>.</p><p> </p><p><em><strong>System Tip: </strong>You can add Weapon to use together with that Technique. Select it on <strong>Details </strong>Tab of that <strong>Techniques</strong>.</em></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Technique Enhancements</span></strong></span></p><ul><li><strong>Brutal Leap:</strong> <strong>(1 SP)</strong> Transfer all of the Falling damage you would usually take into the target instead (see “Falling Attacks” on page 55 for more). </li><li><strong>Heroic Slam:</strong> <strong>(1 SP, 1 AP)</strong> Compare your <strong>Attack Check </strong>against the <strong>PD</strong> of all creatures within 1 Space of you (instead of a single target).</li><li><strong>Far Leap: (1 SP)</strong> Increase your damage by 1 and your Jump Distance by 2.</li></ul>",
